    "narrative": "For the May 2nd slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (86.99) is our undisputed anchor, buoyed by a favorable matchup against Lopez and a substantial park factor boost. While **Lawrence Butler** (70.08) sits on the lower end of the batting order, he is our second-most efficient play today; the combination of a 4.33 xERA matchup against Cecconi and high-upside platoon splits makes him a high-leverage start. We are also leaning on **Geraldo Perdomo** (64.71) and **Will Smith** (63.97), both of whom benefit from top-of-the-order placement and positive environment markers that clear the threshold for strong daily starts.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Jung Hoo Lee** (46.34), who narrowly missed the cut. While his elite speed and leadoff placement are typically prioritized in our strategy, the matchup against Jax and his 3.01 xERA significantly dampened his ceiling compared to starters like **Wenceel Perez** and **Jeremiah Jackson**. Those two, despite lower base projections, offer greater utility due to the \"Slow SP Delivery\" dynamic, which enhances our pursuit of the league\u2019s scarcest category: stolen bases. We are monitoring **Yainer Diaz** (47.40) closely; his efficiency is hampered by a tough matchup against Early, and he represents our most significant risk of falling below the 40-point floor. Meanwhile, we have opted to keep **Daulton Varsho** (39.48) benched, as the combination of an elite arm and poor platoon splits keeps him firmly below our operational threshold.",
